Ingredients.4: 1 (1 ounce) package taco seasoning mix, divided

Ingredients.6: 1 (10.75 ounce) can  condensed nacho cheese soup (such as Campbell's® Fiesta Nacho Cheese Soup)

Ingredients.8: 1 (32 ounce) package frozen bite-size potato nuggets (such as Tater Tots®)

Directions.1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Spray a 9x13-inch casserole dish with cooking spray.

Directions.2: Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat and stir in ground beef, green onion, and 1/2 package taco seasoning. Cook and stir mixture until the beef is crumbly, evenly browned, and no longer pink, about 10 minutes. Drain and discard any excess grease.

Directions.3: Combine remaining taco seasoning mix with tomato soup, nacho cheese soup, and milk in a saucepan; heat soup mixture until just boiling.

Directions.4: Layer potato nuggets in the prepared casserole dish.

Directions.5: Bake in the preheated oven until potato nuggets begin to crisp, about 10 minutes.

Directions.6: Spoon ground beef mixture over potato nuggets; pour in soup mixture.

Directions.7: Bake until soup mixture is bubbling, 15 to 20 minutes. Sprinkle casserole with Mexican cheese blend; bake until cheese is melted, 5 to 10 minutes.
